column5: A buddy of mind caught this at Cordova lake. Hard to tell from pics but this fish doesn't have sucker type mouth. Some of these caught were a foot long. I was thinking it was a chub but not sure. Any ideas what type of fish this is?
Looks like a big creek chub.
I googled creek chub and fall fish and they both look like this fish. Torpedo shaped and the mouth was shallow and very rounded. Black back with silver sides.
Thats a fall fish.  Ive seen them up to 15 16 inches in the ott riv.  Disappointing when youre walleye fishing thats for sure
Fall fish it is. Thanks for educating me
